instNote: ﻿In consequence of St. Mary's in Somerset being destroyed by fire, these Sisters are now conducting their school in the beautiful and commodious building, St. Joseph's College, two miles from Somerset, where they will continue to teach till July 1st, 1867. In July, 1867, the Sisters hope to move to a new and spacious building now in course of erection near Columbus, the capital of Ohio. The Sisters hope to open their school in Columbus in September, A.D. 1867. This Academy will be well provided with competent and experienced teachers, who will spare no efforts to make their Institution worthy of extensive patronage. Number of professed sisters in the Institution, 18; novices, 8. Number of pupils last year, 134.
